      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MONTY MONTE (4) produced a better effort last start when runner-up over 1800m at this track, beaten a nose after racing handy then finding the lead only to be bloused late. Finds a nice race and will prove very tough to beat once more. MAJESTIC TUSSLE (1) led at the bell but then broke gear and galloped last start and finished a distant seventh on debut in a 2230m event at this track two weeks ago. Has the benefit of a good draw. Meets a similar line up and is worth another chance. IVAR (2) was responsible for a better effort last time out when third over 2230m at this track after having led at the bell. Should run a big race. PERSEVERANSE (5) must be included on the back of some solid recent form, most recently when third at this track over 1800m.",
